SIMPLE: mirthful
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mirthful
<hw>Mirth"ful</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Full of
mirth or merriment; merry; <as>as, <ex>mirthful</ex>
children</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Indicating or inspiring mirth; <as>as, a
<ex>mirthful</ex> face</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Mirthful</qex>, comic shows.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Mirth"ful*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Mirth"ful*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mirthless</ent>⟦br⟧
